line.comment: * To edit setting of the ship controlled by chief
* This variable kept until interface closed (yeah, each open will reset it)
* Add menu info line base on $Base.TextID + 1
* Open menu with title based on $Base.TextID + 2
* This way does not works for zeros searching. Will always false :(
* In: $args array of list, text id, return value
* $Dummy = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=35510, $Dummy, null, null, null, null
* add custom menu item to array $Menu: text=$Dummy returnvalue='BuyingPrice'
* $Dummy = sprintf: pageid=$PageID textid=35512, $Dummy, null, null, null, null
* add custom menu item to array $Menu: text=$Dummy returnvalue='SellingPrice'
* Restart all subordinates which running currently.
* Select program and switch ship to the program if selected.
* Out: $SelectedOption - selected program number or null if program was
* Build list of main type ID: for tradeable wares.
* Out: $MainTypes - Array of main type ID.
* Add ware to current wares list. Skip if ware already added.
* In: $id - Text ID of price request dialog.
* In: $var - Index of array element to set.
* In: $id - Text ID of value request dialog.
* In: $var - Index of array element to set.
* = [THIS]-> call script 'wwsl.T2.function3' : fn=8202 arg1=$WareStruct arg2=$cWareStr.MinToBuyLimit arg3=$r
* Make list of stations, using conditional selection.
* Menu to copy settings to current ship from another
* Sort data and add as menu options.
